This scrip has reading an email.eml file , every small blue-team script follows this patterns:
open file
read lines
for each line:
    check condition
    if match:
        store result
print summary
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
üîÅ Step 3: Loop Practice (Core Skill)
You‚Äôll use something like:
  - A for loop to read lines
  -if statements to detect patterns
Things to practice detecting inside the loop:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pattern         |       Why
"From:"	               Sender identity
"Reply-To:"	           Often mismatched in phishing
"http"	               URLs
"Content-Type:         application/zip"	Suspicious attachment
"X-Originating-IP"	   Real sender IP
"Urgent"	             Social engineering
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What each part means (important)
Part	            |     Meaning
open()	                Opens the file
"email.eml"	            File name (must be in your current directory)
"r"	                    Read mode
encoding="utf-8"	      Handles text correctly
errors="ignore"	        Skips broken characters
as f	                  f is now the file object
readlines()	            Reads file into a list of lines
